Package: statguide
Type: Package
Title: Simple Guide to Basic Statistical Tests
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Ada", "Vestli",
      email = "adves1313@uib.no",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: This package provides a simple guidance tool that helps beginners choose, understand, and run basic statistical tests. The package supports learning and decision-making by guiding users through test selection, explanation, diagnostics, and execution. It handles a limited set of introductory-level scenarios and requires explicit specification of outcome and predictor variables to avoid incorrect assumptions about variable roles. Supported analyses include t-tests, ANOVA, correlation, chi-square tests, and logistic regression. More advanced methods such as mixed-effects models, repeated-measures designs, survival analysis, and multivariate techniques are intentionally outside the scope. The aim is to provide clear, structured guidance for common and unambiguous statistical situations.
